    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors and determined that the overall evidence package supports an Accepted decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU. The Test conditions factor achieved level 2 against a required level 3, which is acknowledged as a gap; however, the team judged that the single F1717 configuration is the primary regulatory submission scenario and that the validation evidence for that configuration is robust (E/uval <1.96 for all QoIs). The team did not specifically address the unassessed Numerical solver error factor in the decision rationale, as solver convergence was assumed adequate based on engineering judgment without formal documentation. The package is submitted with modelRiskLevel 3 and the decision is Accepted.",
